InvalidTokenTypeException
          Thrown when either the issued token from the server does not match the predefined or any known token type.
OAuthException
          Parent class for all OAuth 2.0 specific exceptions.
UnauthorizedClientException
          This Exception is thrown either, when the client fails to present a valid authorization to the server or if the server expects another type of authorization.
UnsupportedGrantTypeException
          Thrown when the client uses an unsupported type of authorization to the server.
